
"You know I would, I always understand," I remark.
"No Summer, usually you don't. Can we just drop this." I saw him getting frustrated.
As much as I wanted to go on and ask him, I don't. I wasn't in his place to want to be questioned at that moment so I changed the topic.
"Want to do something we'll probably regret later." I more likely stated than asked.
